cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.NI 

This paper is primarily focused on the analysis and classification of malware, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of n-gram document classification techniques also suggests a potential overlap with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the implementation of a prototype system, which could be considered a software engineering (cs.SE) project. Finally, the focus on network events and the use of network-based behavioral artifacts suggests a potential overlap with networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
